Colombian and Ecuadorian Anacroneuria (Plecoptera: Perlidae): seven new species, records and life stagesAbstract From Colombia and Ecuador seven new species of stoneflies are described: Anacroneuria arcabuco, A. cajas, A. chachis, A. choco, A. iguaque, A. mindo and A. paisa. New records are also presented for A. azul Rojas & Baena, A. bifasciata (Pictet) A. calima Baena & Rojas, A. caraca Stark, A. fenestrata (Pictet), A. quilla Stark & Zúñiga, A. ricki Zúñiga & Stark, A. socapa Stark & Zúñiga, and A. yameo Stark & Sivec. In addition, the previously unknown females of A. anchicaya Baena & Zúñiga, A. jewetti Stark and A. portilla Stark & Rojas are described.